div.p:
               We have by last mail notice of the arrival of the Dover Castle in June in London. You will remember that I wrote not only by the ships mail but also by the 4 subsequent mails, that I had made arrangements of sending this special consignment under the care of the Surgeon of the ship Dr Thomson;

See M to W. Hooker, 24 April 1862 (in this edition as 62-04-24f); M to G. Bentham, 23 May 1862; M to G. Bentham, 24 June 1862 (in this edition as 62-06-24b); M to G. Bentham, 24 July 1862 (in this edition as 62-07-24a); and M to J. Hooker, 22 June 1862.
                but I shall not run the risk again of forwarding anything again without bill of loading, may the opportunity be ever so favorable.
